http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/145-English-medium-residential-schools-to-open-across-State/article13981865.ece

Minister for Social Welfare H. Anjaneya on Monday said 145 residential English-medium schools would open across the State from the next academic year, from Class 6 to 10.Each school will accommodate 250 students and have 11 teaching and 16 non-teaching faculty. The Karnataka Public Service Commission (KPSC) will be asked to recruit the teachers. Addressing presspersons here, Mr. Anjaneya said each school would be established on 10 acres of land at a cost of Rs. 10 crore to Rs. 15 crore.The proposed residential school will also have activities related to farming, animal husbandry, gym, and a library for ensuring integrated education for children. Deputy commissioners, MLAs and MLCs have been asked to identify land for the schools. Compensation based on present market value would be provided to landowners, he said. Mr. Anjaneya also said 100 post-matric hostels, each for boys and girls, would be constructed before the commencement of the next academic year, and cost of each hostel would be Rs. 3 crore. Wardens, cooks and security personnel would be recruited for each hostel.Following the High Court of Karnataka verdict, he said services of 409 teachers of the Morarji Desai School would be regularised. Teachers were hired on ad-hoc basis about four years ago.Each school to have 250 students, 11 teaching and16 non-teaching members